vclaim: Some 2,600 uncounted votes, a majority of which were cast for U.S. President Donald Trump, were found in Floyd County, Georgia, moving the president about 800 votes closer to President-elect Joe Biden's tally in the 2020 general election.
title: Were 2,600 Uncounted Votes Found in Floyd County, Georgia?
subtitle: The discovery was made during a state audit, which is different than a recount.
author: Jordan Liles
